    {
      "id": "4d861256_94d669ae",
      "file_path": "docs/deployment.rst",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 104,
      "message": "When Krzysztof reviewed cps temporal creditentials, he was interested in having some documentation related to external secrets then I added the following in cps temporal. Do we want to have it here now ?\n\n---\nApplication and database credentials are kept in Kubernetes secrets. They are\ndefined as external secrets in\n`values.yaml <https://github.com/onap/oom/blob/master/kubernetes/cps/components/cps-temporal/values.yaml#L28>`_\nfile.\n\nThen, credential values from these secrets are configured in running container\nas environment variables. This is done in\n`deployment.yaml <https://github.com/onap/oom/blob/master/kubernetes/cps/components/cps-temporal/templates/deployment.yaml#L47>`_\nfile.\n\nIf no specific passwords are provided to the chart as override values for\ndeployment, then passwords are automatically generated when deploying and\ncreating Helm release.\n---",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-05 12:56:22.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
